## 🟠 MEDIUM Severity

### 3. Missing Security Headers

**Issue:** No HTTP security headers are set. This exposes users to clickjacking, MIME-type sniffing, and cross-site scripting attacks via the browser.

**OWASP:** [A05:2021 – Security Misconfiguration](https://owasp.org/Top10/A05_2021-Security_Misconfiguration/)

**Recommendation:** Use `helmet`:

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet());
```

This automatically sets `X-Frame-Options`, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, `Content-Security-Policy`, and others.

---

### 4. No CORS Policy

**Issue:** By default, Express doesn't set CORS headers, which means either all origins are implicitly blocked or, if `cors()` middleware is later added carelessly with `origin: '*'`, all origins will be allowed — both are problematic.

**OWASP:** [A05:2021 – Security Misconfiguration](https://owasp.org/Top10/A05_2021-Security_Misconfiguration/)

**Recommendation:** Explicitly configure CORS with an allowlist:

```js
const cors = require('cors');

app.use(cors({
  origin: ['https://yourapp.example.com'],
  methods: ['GET', 'POST'],
  allowedHeaders: ['Authorization', 'Content-Type'],
}));
```

