### 4. No Rate Limiting
**OWASP:** A04 – Insecure Design

All endpoints are unbounded. A single client can hammer the server with thousands of requests per second — either for DoS or to brute-force tokens/credentials once auth is added.

```js
// ✅ Apply rate limiting
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');

const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes
  max: 100,                  // max 100 requests per window per IP
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
});

app.use(limiter);
